{
  "version": 1,
  "name": "Hardware date display — \"0611\" (June 11)",
  "description": "A hardware-only date display: four CD4511 BCD-to-7-segment decoders drive four common-cathode 7-segment displays through 330R segment resistors, spelling \"0611\" (June 11, MMDD). Each decoder's BCD inputs A-D are hardwired to the +5V/ground rails in the digit's BCD pattern (0=0000, 6=0110, 1=0001), LT and BL are tied high (inactive) and LE low (transparent), so the date appears with no microcontroller at all. All four digits fit on one 63-column breadboard.",
